Mombasa Senator Omar Hassan has criticised the Health ministry for threatening to take action against the media for exposing corruption in the docket.He said all public servants must be open to scrutiny and once accused of corruption, the onus is on them to prove themselves clean.The Business Daily last week reported that an internal audit in the ministry revealed possible misappropriation of Sh5.2 billion, but the ministry has denied the reports, saying Sh3.1 billion may have been lost.The ministry threatened to take legal action against the Nation Media Group for depicting the government as corrupt.&ldquo;Any person in public service, [Health PS Nicholas] Muraguri included, must be very open to media scrutiny,&rdquo; Omar said.He spoke on Friday during a training for the KPJA members on effective coverage of the Senate.